    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2006-05-03</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2006-05-26T19:37:48Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow low and moderate income taxpayers without health insurance a refundable tax credit for 90% of the cost of high deductible health insurance (up to $3,000) to provide coverage for the taxpayer, the taxpayer's spouse, and dependents. </p><p> Directs the Secretary of the Treasury to establish a program for making advance payment of tax credit amounts to health insurance providers. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>A bill to amend the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 to provide a refundable credit for high deductible health plans for uninsured individuals.</title>
